Recap:
    *Cucumber: it is a tool that supports Behavior-driven development (BDD)
    *Gherkin language is used to write BDD
    *Keywords of Gherkin: Feature, Scenario, Given, When, Then, And

What is Framework:
    *It is an organized structure which allows us to write clean and maintainable code
    *Functionality is key.

    Features File --> declare the steps inside
    Runner Class --> allows us to execute all the features/scenarios desired at same time
    Steps (created under java since it contains java code) --> contains step definitions

POM:
    *Page Object Model is a design pattern in which we create object repository


    Cross-browser Testing: Testing across multiple browsers (Chrome, Safari, Edge, Firefox)